AFRICAN SWINE FEVER - ASIA (48): NORTH KOREA (CHAGANG-DO) DOMESTIC, 1ST REPORT, OIE
***********************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 30 May 2019
Source: OIE, WAHIS (World Animal Health Information System), weekly disease information 2019 [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=30664


African swine fever [ASF], Korea (Dem People's Rep)
---------------------------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 30 May 2019 from Mr Ri Kyong Gun, director of the Veterinary and, Ministry of Agriculture, Anti-Epizootic Department, Pyongyang, Korea (Dem People's Rep.)

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 23 May 2019
Date of confirmation of the event: 25 May 2019
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease in the country
Causal agent: African swine fever virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced), necropsy
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks: 1
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak location: Buksang cooperative farm, Ri, Usi, Chagang-Do
Date of start of the outbreak: 23 May 2019
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Swine / 99 / 77 / 77 / 22 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Swine / 78 / 78 / 100 / 100
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone; surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; official destruction of animal products; official disposal of carcasses, by-products, and waste; stamping out; disinfection; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Central veterinary station of Ministry of Agriculture (national laboratory) / swine / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 25 May 2019 / positive
Veterinary Research Institute of Academy of Agriculture Science (AAS) (national laboratory) / swine / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 25 May 2019 / positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Unfortunately, this report officially confirms the presence of African swine fever in North Korea. According to the report published in ProMED-mail posting 20190430.6449134, the virus has been suspected of circulating in the country since mid-February 2019.

See map of ASF in Asia (August 2018 to date) at http://www.fao.org/ag/againfo/programmes/en/empres/ASF/img/2019/map1_2019_05_23.jpg. - Mod.CRD

HealthMap/ProMED-mail map: Chagang province, North Korea: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6494781,16605.]
